column1: The Rounding Rules are defined by three parameters separated by dashes: X-Y-Z.
- The first parameter (X) corresponds to the Minimum Duration. It specifies the minimum duration before a call can be charged or rated.
- The second parameter (Y) corresponds to the Initial Rounding. It specifies the initial rounding after a call has passed the minimum duration threshold.
- The third and last parameter (Z) corresponds to the Additional Rounding. It specifies the additional rounding that will be applied to the call once it has gone past the initial rounding threshold.
